.TH "prandom_bytes_state" 9 "prandom_bytes_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
prandom_bytes_state \- get the requested number of pseudo-random bytes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" prandom_bytes_state
.BI "(struct rnd_state *state "  ","
.BI "void *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t bytes "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "state" 12
pointer to state structure holding seeded state.
.IP "buf" 12
where to copy the pseudo-random bytes to
.IP "bytes" 12
the requested number of bytes

This is used for pseudo-randomness with no outside seeding.
For more random results, use \fBprandom_bytes\fP.
